{"search_data": "TelanganaChristmas Gift Scheme 2017 Launched by KCR in Telangana for Poor PeopleThis scheme is launched to provide Christmas Gifts which includes clothes and dinner to the weaker sections of the Telangana state.Under this scheme, the state will ensure that the distributed clothes are of high quality.As per the collected data, there are around 1 lakh Christians in Hyderabad and Secunderabad city and 1 lakh in rest of the state. So this scheme will benefit around 2 lakh Christians belonging to the weaker sections.Subsequently, MLAs and Corporates along with the Christian Organizations are given the responsibility to identify beneficiaries.After the identification of beneficiaries, govt. will transfer the specified amount directly to the account of the church. These churches will hand over the gift hampers and organize the dinner facility.Accordingly, the state govt. has identified 190 churches to avail the benefits of this scheme.The state govt. firstly launches this scheme in December 2015 and is now going to continue this scheme.Furthermore, CM will also host a grand dinner party for some best Christian families in Hyderabad on the Christmas eve."}